ðŸ“š Course Contents  

### I. Cybersecurity Fundamentals  
- Introduction to Cybersecurity  
- The **CIA Triad** (Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability)  
- Common **Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Risks**  
- **Security Frameworks** (ISO, NIST, CIS, etc.)  

---

 II. Networking Essentials  
- **OSI Model** & **TCP/IP** Concepts  
- **Ports and Protocols** (HTTP, HTTPS, FTP, DNS, SSH, SMTP)  
- **Subnetting, Routing, Firewalls, NAT**  
- Network Monitoring Tools (**Wireshark**, **Nmap**)  

---

III. Cyber Attacks & Defense  
- **Malware Types** (Viruses, Worms, Trojans, Ransomware)  
- **Social Engineering** & **Phishing**  
- **DDoS Attacks** & **Botnets**  
- **Endpoint Protection** & **Firewall Configuration**  

---

 IV. Ethical Hacking & Penetration Testing  
- **Footprinting & Reconnaissance**  
- **Network Scanning Techniques**  
- **Exploitation and Payloads**  
- **Maintaining Access & Covering Tracks**  

---

 V. Security Tools  
- **Kali Linux Basics**  
- **Metasploit**, **Burp Suite**, **Wireshark**, **Hydra**  
- **Password Cracking Tools** (Hashcat, John the Ripper)  
- **Security Automation** (Python Scripts, Bash Tools)  

